There are a number of detection and monitoring devices and alarms designed to ensure the continued safe operation of Water Reclamation Plant No. 9.  These devices are located throughout the Plant and monitor various aspects of Plant Operations.  

Alarms
WRP No. 9 is equipped with Leak Detectors that are designed to detect chlorine in the chlorine storage and use areas at or above 1-ppm.  When one of these detectors senses a gas leak at or above 1.0-ppm, audible alarms activate locally and an alarm is transmitted to District Control at Headquarters.  At 3-ppm the visual alarm (beacon light) on top of the building is activated.  Ventilation fans in the chlorinator room run constantly 24-hours per day.  The alarms can only be reset and cleared after the leak detectors sense less than 1-ppm of gas.  The alarms are tested by District Operators twice each month.  Additionally, the District¿s Communications Shop inspects, tests and calibrates the chlorine alarm system on a monthly schedule.  

